<inglise> Understanding on the Interpretation of Article XVII of the General Agreement on Tariffs And Trade 1994 </inglise>
<eesti> vl9 RT II 1999, 22, 123 K&Auml;SITUSLEPE GATT 1994 XVII ARTIKLI T&Otilde;LGENDAMISE KOHTA </eesti>
<inglise> Members, </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmed, </eesti>
<inglise> Noting that Article XVII provides for obligations on Members in respect of the activities of the state trading enterprises referred to in paragraph 1 of Article XVII, which are required to be consistent with the general principles of non-discriminatory treatment prescribed in GATT 1994 for governmental measures affecting imports or exports by private traders; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;rkides, et XVII artiklis on s&auml;testatud liikmete kohustused XVII artikli l&otilde;ikes 1 viidatud riiklike kaubandusettev&otilde;tete tegevuse suhtes, mille puhul n&otilde;utakse vastavust diskrimineerimisvaba re&zcaron;iimi &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tetele, mis on ette n&auml;htud GATTis 1994 erasektori kaubandusettev&otilde;tjate importi ja eksporti m&otilde;jutavate riiklike meetmete suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> Noting further that Members are subject to their GATT 1994 obligations in respect of those governmental measures affecting state trading enterprises; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;rkides veel, et riiklikke kaubandusettev&otilde;tteid m&otilde;jutavate riiklike meetmete suhtes kehtivad liikmete kohustused GATT 1994 alusel; </eesti>
<inglise> Recognizing that this Understanding is without prejudice to the substantive disciplines prescribed in Article XVII; </inglise>
<eesti> t&otilde;dedes, et k&auml;esolev k&auml;situslepe ei kahjusta XVII artiklis ette n&auml;htud oluliste p&otilde;him&otilde;tete rakendamist, </eesti>
<inglise> Hereby agree as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> lepivad kokku j&auml;rgmises. </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to ensure the transparency of the activities of state trading enterprises, Members shall notify such enterprises to the Council for Trade in Goods, for review by the working party to be set up under paragraph 5, in accordance with the following working definition: </inglise>
<eesti> Tagamaks selguse riiklike kaubandusettev&otilde;tete tegevuses, teatavad liikmed need ettev&otilde;tted kaubavahetuse n&otilde;ukogule (l&auml;bivaatamiseks l&otilde;ike 5 alusel loodavas toimkonnas), l&auml;htudes j&auml;rgmisest t&ouml;&ouml;m&auml;&auml;ratlusest: </eesti>
<inglise> "Governmental and non-governmental enterprises, including marketing boards, which have been granted exclusive or special rights or privileges, including statutory or constitutional powers, in the exercise of which they influence through their purchases or sales the level or direction of imports or exports." </inglise>
<eesti> "Riiklikud ja mitteriiklikud ettev&otilde;tted, sealhulgas turustusorganisatsioonid, millele on antud eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igused v&otilde;i -privileegid, sealhulgas seadusj&auml;rgsed v&otilde;i konstitutsioonilised volitused, mida t&auml;ites nad oma ostu v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;gi kaudu m&otilde;jutavad impordi v&otilde;i ekspordi taset v&otilde;i suunda." </eesti>
<inglise> This notification requirement does not apply to imports of products for immediate or ultimate consumption in governmental use or in use by an enterprise as specified above and not otherwise for resale or use in the production of goods for sale. </inglise>
<eesti> See teatamisn&otilde;ue ei kehti nende toodete impordi puhul, mis on m&auml;&auml;ratud koheseks v&otilde;i l&otilde;plikuks tarbimiseks valitsuses v&otilde;i eespool piiritletud ettev&otilde;ttes ja mis pole m&auml;&auml;ratud edasim&uuml;&uuml;giks v&otilde;i kaupade tootmiseks m&uuml;&uuml;gi jaoks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member shall conduct a review of its policy with regard to the submission of notifications on state trading enterprises to the Council for Trade in Goods, taking account of the provisions of this Understanding. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva k&auml;situsleppe s&auml;tteid arvesse v&otilde;ttes vaatab iga liige l&auml;bi oma poliitika riiklikke ettev&otilde;tteid puudutavate teadete kaubavahetuse n&otilde;ukogule esitamise suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> In carrying out such a review, each Member should have regard to the need to ensure the maximum transparency possible in its notifications so as to permit a clear appreciation of the manner of operation of the enterprises notified and the effect of their operations on international trade. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellisel l&auml;bivaatusel peaks iga liige arvesse v&otilde;tma vajadust tagada oma teadete v&otilde;imalikult suur selgus, v&otilde;imaldamaks selge hinnangu andmist teatatud ettev&otilde;tete tegutsemisviisi ning nende tegevuse m&otilde;ju suhtes rahvusvahelisele kaubandusele. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Notifications shall be made in accordance with the questionnaire on state trading adopted on 24 May 1960 (BISD 9S/184-185), it being understood that Members shall notify the enterprises referred to in paragraph 1 whether or not imports or exports have in fact taken place. </inglise>
<eesti> Teated esitatakse koosk&otilde;las riiklikku kaubandust puudutava k&uuml;sitluslehega (BISD 9S/184-185), mis v&otilde;eti vastu 24. mail 1960, kusjuures ollakse seisukohal, et liikmed teatavad l&otilde;ikes 1 viidatud ettev&otilde;tted olenemata sellest, kas import v&otilde;i eksport on tegelikult aset leidnud v&otilde;i mitte. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Any Member which has reason to believe that another Member has not adequately met its notification obligation may raise the matter with the Member concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liige, kel on p&otilde;hjust arvata, et teine liige ei ole oma teatamiskohustust asjakohaselt t&auml;itnud, v&otilde;ib t&otilde;statada selle k&uuml;simuse asjaomase liikme ees. </eesti>
<inglise> If the matter is not satisfactorily resolved it may make a counter-notification to the Council for Trade in Goods, for consideration by the working party set up under paragraph 5, simultaneously informing the Member concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui k&uuml;simust rahuldavalt ei lahendata, v&otilde;ib ta esitada kaubavahetuse n&otilde;ukogule vastuteate, et l&otilde;ike 5 alusel loodud toimkond selle l&auml;bi vaataks, teatades sellest samaaegselt ka asjaomasele liikmele. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> A working party shall be set up, on behalf of the Council for Trade in Goods, to review notifications and counter-notifications. </inglise>
<eesti> Kaubavahetuse n&otilde;ukogu nimel moodustatakse toimkond, kes vaatab l&auml;bi teated ja vastuteated. </eesti>
<inglise> In the light of this review and without prejudice to paragraph 4(c) of Article XVII, the Council for Trade in Goods may make recommendations with regard to the adequacy of notifications and the need for further information. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle l&auml;bivaatamise taustal ja m&otilde;jutamata XVII artikli l&otilde;ike 4 punkti c kohaldamist v&otilde;ib kaubavahetuse n&otilde;ukogu anda soovitusi teadete asjakohasuse ja vajaduse kohta lisateabe j&auml;rele. </eesti>
<inglise> The working party shall also review, in the light of the notifications received, the adequacy of the above-mentioned questionnaire on state trading and the coverage of state trading enterprises notified under paragraph 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Samuti vaatab toimkond saadud teadetest l&auml;htudes l&auml;bi eespool nimetatud, riiklikku kaubandust puudutava k&uuml;sitluslehe asjakohasuse ning l&otilde;ike 1 alusel teatatud riiklike kaubandusettev&otilde;tete h&otilde;lmatuse. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall also develop an illustrative list showing the kinds of relationships between governments and enterprises, and the kinds of activities, engaged in by these enterprises, which may be relevant for the purposes of Article XVII. </inglise>
<eesti> Samuti t&ouml;&ouml;tab toimkond v&auml;lja selgitusloendi, milles on n&auml;idatud valitsuste ja ettev&otilde;tete vaheliste suhete ja nende ettev&otilde;tete tegevuse laad, mis v&otilde;ib olla asjakohane XVII artikli raames. </eesti>
<inglise> It is understood that the Secretariat will provide a general background paper for the working party on the operations of state trading enterprises as they relate to international trade. </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;istetakse, et sekretariaat esitab toimkonnale &uuml;ldise taustdokumendi riiklike kaubandusettev&otilde;tete tegevuse kohta rahvusvahelises kaubanduses. Toimkonda v&otilde;ivad kuuluda k&otilde;ik liikmed, kes avaldavad soovi selle t&ouml;&ouml;s osaleda. </eesti>
<inglise> Membership of the working party shall be open to all Members indicating their wish to serve on it. </inglise>
<eesti> Toimkond tuleb kokku aasta jooksul alates WTO lepingu j&otilde;ustumise kuup&auml;evast ning p&auml;rast seda v&auml;hemalt kord aastas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall meet within a year of the date of entry into force of the WTO Agreement and thereafter at least once a year. It shall report annually to the Council for Trade in Goods. </inglise>
<eesti> Igal aastal esitab toimkond aruanded kaubavahetuse n&otilde;ukogule (1). (1) K&otilde;nealuse toimkonna tegevus tuleb koosk&otilde;lastada t&ouml;&ouml;r&uuml;hma omaga, mis on s&auml;testatud 15. aprillil 1994 vastu v&otilde;etud teatamisprotseduure k&auml;sitleva ministrite otsuse III osas. </eesti>
 